Here's Me!

My Education

I am pursuing my Master's in Computer Science at Arizona State University. I focus on Natural Language Processing and Machine Learning.

Current Position

I presently work as a Full-stack engineer at the Decision Theater in ASU on analytics projects for Arizona Schools and Adidas. Previously, I worked for 3+ years as a Full-stack software engineer at Unisys biometric and biographic based identity management solutions

My Choice of Poison

I primarily work on Python and Java based frameworks for general programming, data analysis and modeling, and deep learning.

Career

A brief timeline of my career so far in Computer Science

  • 2010-2014

    Bachelor's in Computer Science and Engineering

    I pursued my Bachelor's in Computer Science and Engineering in Bangalore Institute of Technology - Bangalore, India.

  • 2014-2017

    Software Engineer at Unisys

    My work experience began through a Software Engineer position in Unisys. I worked as a Full-Stack engineer on the Java and MEAN frameworks. The projects I was involved with here were based on the Stealth Identity product in the Biometric Identification and Credentialing domain. I was a key part of three client deliverable identity management solutions, and research/development projects to enhance the biometric device handlers used in the product frameworks

  • January 2018 - Present

    Master's in Computer Science

    My desire to branch out to the domain of machine learning and natural language processing led me to pursue a Master's degree at Arizona State University. Apart from these domains, my coursework included planning and learning of robots and data visualization. I'm currently working on my Master's thesis to create a question answering system using a generate-validate approach based on BERT transformers and knowledge reasoning

  • July 2019 - Present

    Full-Stack Developer at Decision Theater - ASU

    My second stint with software development at the Decision Theater has provided me the opportunity to work on machine learning and new technologies like docker, kubernetes, terraform and SQLAlchemy. In a short period of time, I've worked on multiple projects primarily based on python frameworks.

  • Hopefully,
    More to
    come!
